HEADWORD: Polycotyledonary
<hw>Pol`y*cot`y*led"on*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>cotyledonary</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the villi of the placenta collected into
definite patches, or cotyledons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

